"title": "5970: unhappiness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5970: unhappiness",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A sense of despondency or sadness, often linked with disappointment or loss. Scripture documents human unhappiness in response to a number of situations, while recalling God's unhappiness over the folly and rebelliousness of sinful humanity.</p>\n<h2>Unhappiness as the result of adverse circumstances</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps90:10\">PSA 90:10</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:21-Matt26:22\">MAT 26:21–26:22</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:19\">MRK 14:19</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:34-Gen26:35\">GEN 26:34–26:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen40:6-Gen40:7\">GEN 40:6–40:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:24\">GEN 42:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:8\">1SA 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam1:15\">1SA 1:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh1:4\">NEH 1:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh2:1-Neh2:3\">NEH 2:1–2:3</a> <em>Artaxerxes queries Nehemiah's sadness</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job17:7\">JOB 17:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job30:25\">JOB 30:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:1\">PSA 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps13:2\">PSA 13:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:9\">PSA 31:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:21\">PRO 17:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov17:25\">PRO 17:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa19:8-Isa19:10\">ISA 19:8–19:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer45:3\">JER 45:3</a></p>\n<h2>Unhappiness caused by loss</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:1\">2SA 19:1</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:5-John16:6\">JHN 16:5–16:6</a></strong> <em>Jesus Christ had just foretold his departure.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:12\">GEN 38:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen42:38\">GEN 42:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen48:7\">GEN 48:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam1:26\">2SA 1:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam14:2\">2SA 14:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Joel1:8\">JOL 1:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt17:23\">MAT 17:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:45\">LUK 22:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:17\">LUK 24:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John20:11\">JHN 20:11</a> <em>Mary weeps at Jesus Christ's tomb</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:38\">ACT 20:38</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:27\">PHP 2:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:13\">1TH 4:13</a></p>\n<h2>Unhappiness over failure and sin</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek9:4\">EZK 9:4</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor5:1-1Cor5:2\">1CO 5:1–5:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:39\">NUM 14:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg20:26\">JDG 20:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg21:6\">JDG 21:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:33\">1SA 2:33</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:9-Neh8:11\">NEH 8:9–8:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps88:1-Ps88:9\">PSA 88:1–88:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps107:39\">PSA 107:39</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam1:4-Lam1:5\">LAM 1:4–1:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek21:6-Ezek21:7\">EZK 21:6–21:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech12:10\">ZEC 12:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:3\">MAT 27:3</a> <em>Judas seized with remorse at his betrayal of Jesus Christ</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:62\">LUK 22:62</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:2\">ROM 9:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor2:2-2Cor2:5\">2CO 2:2–2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:8-2Cor7:11\">2CO 7:8–7:11</a></p>\n<h2>Unhappiness caused by a person's own selfishness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:10\">1TI 6:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs21:4\">1KI 21:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Esth6:12\">EST 6:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov23:29-Prov23:30\">PRO 23:29–23:30</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:22\">MAT 19:22</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:22\">MRK 10:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:23\">LUK 18:23</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ knew unhappiness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:35\">JHN 11:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:38\">MAT 26:38</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:34\">MRK 14:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John11:33\">JHN 11:33</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:27\">JHN 12:27</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John13:21\">JHN 13:21</a></p>\n<h2>God also grieves</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:6-Gen6:7\">GEN 6:6–6:7</a></strong> <em>Prior to the flood</em>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:30\">EPH 4:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen18:20\">GEN 18:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:11\">1SA 15:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam15:35\">1SA 15:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam24:16\">2SA 24:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:40\">PSA 78:40</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:10\">ISA 63:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer42:10\">JER 42:10</a></p>\n<h2>God's remedy for unhappiness</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:32-Lam3:33\">LAM 3:32–3:33</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:6\">1PE 1:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps6:7-Ps6:8\">PSA 6:7–6:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:14\">PSA 10:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps31:9\">PSA 31:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps116:1-Ps116:6\">PSA 116:1–116:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa35:10\">ISA 35:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa51:11\">ISA 51:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa60:20\">ISA 60:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa61:1-Isa61:3\">ISA 61:1–61:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer8:18\">JER 8:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:12-Jer31:13\">JER 31:12–31:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:20-John16:22\">JHN 16:20–16:22</a></p>",
